### Panel Splitter — Webtoon Mode

#### [MODIFY] [panelSplitter.js](file:///c:/Users/parvi/Documents/animereels/server/services/panelSplitter.js)

For webtoon strips, skip gutter-based splitting. Produce ONE "panel" per page (the full page acts as the unit):

```diff
 async function detectPanels(imagePath) {
   const { width, height } = await image.metadata();
+  
+  // Webtoon strips: keep as single unit (camera scrolls through it)
+  if (height / width >= 2.0) {
+    return { 
+      panels: [{ x: 0, y: 0, w: width, h: height }], 
+      width, height,
+      isWebtoon: true 
+    };
+  }
   
   // ... existing gutter detection for manga ...
 }
```

This means timeline builder gets 1 entry per webtoon page (longer duration) instead of 3-4 sub-panels (shorter durations). Each entry gets enough time for a meaningful scroll-through.

---

### Timeline Builder Awareness

#### [MODIFY] [timelineBuilder.js](file:///c:/Users/parvi/Documents/animereels/server/services/timelineBuilder.js)

No major changes needed. When panelSplitter produces 1 panel per webtoon page, the timeline builder naturally allocates more time per entry. A 67-page chapter with 1 panel/page at 5 minutes = ~4.5s per page — perfect for a scroll-through.

Minor addition: pass `isWebtoon` flag through to timeline entries so the renderer can check it.

---

## Edge Cases Handled

| Scenario | How it's handled |
|---|---|
| **Mixed format chapter** (some manga pages, some webtoon strips) | Per-page detection via `isWebtoonStrip()` — each page takes the right path |
| **Very tall strips** (ratio > 4:1) | More interest points requested, slower scroll speed |
| **Strip with few interesting areas** | `buildScrollPath` injects synthetic waypoints to ensure smooth coverage |
| **Very short clip duration** (< 2s for a strip) | Falls back to single zoom on highest-importance point |
| **No AI available** | Default scroll path: top→middle→bottom with uniform zoom 2.0 |
| **Seamless art (no gutters)** | This is the NORM for webtoon — our system doesn't need gutters at all |

